BT /F2 16 Tf 72.0 720.0 Td (Standard Operating Procedure: Automated Procurement) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 72.0 698.0 Td (Workflow) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 72.0 670.0 Td (Document ID: SOP-PROC-001   |   Type: SOP   |   Effective: 2024-03-01) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 640.0 Td (STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURE: AUTOMATED PROCUREMENT WORKFLOW) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 624.0 Td (Document ID: SOP-PROC-001) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 608.0 Td (Version: 2.0) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 592.0 Td (Effective Date: 2024-03-01) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 576.0 Td (Owner: Procurement Operations Lead) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 552.0 Td (1. PURPOSE) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 536.0 Td (This SOP describes the end-to-end steps of the automated procurement workflow) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 520.0 Td (executed by the supply chain AI system. It is intended for operations staff who) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 504.0 Td (monitor the system and for auditors reviewing procurement decisions.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 72.0 480.0 Td (2. WORKFLOW OVERVIEW) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 464.0 Td (The automated procurement workflow is triggered when the system detects that on-) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 448.0 Td (hand inventory for a tracked material is forecast to fall below safety stock) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 432.0 Td (within the next planning horizon \(30 days\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 408.0 Td (Step 1 \20024 Inventory Check: The system retrieves current on-hand quantities and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 392.0 Td (safety stock levels from the SAP inventory module.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 376.0 Td (Step 2 \20024 Demand Forecast: The system analyses 18 months of shipment history to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 360.0 Td (produce a next-month demand forecast with confidence bounds.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 344.0 Td (Step 3 \20024 Procurement Proposal: If forecast demand exceeds on-hand stock, the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 328.0 Td (system generates a purchase requisition proposal including recommended quantity,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 312.0 Td (preferred vendor, unit price, and total estimated cost.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 296.0 Td (Step 4 \20024 Policy Evaluation: The proposal is evaluated against current procurement) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 280.0 Td (approval policies \(see POL-PROC-001 and POL-PROC-002\). The evaluation engine) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 264.0 Td (applies rules in the following priority order:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 248.0 Td (  \(a\) Forbidden vendor check \20024 deny if vendor is on the Restricted Vendor) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 232.0 Td (List.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 216.0 Td (  \(b\) Threshold check \20024 apply the approval tier matching the estimated cost.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 200.0 Td (  \(c\) Vendor constraint check \20024 verify preferred vendor requirement is met.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72.0 184.0 Td (Step 5 \20024 Outcome:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 168.0 Td (  - Auto-approved: a purchase order is created automatically in SAP.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 152.0 Td (  - Needs human approval: the requisition is placed in the approval queue and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 136.0 Td (the responsible manager is notified.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 120.0 Td (  - Denied: the workflow terminates and the operations team is notified to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 83.0 104.0 Td (intervene manually.) Tj ET
endstream
